<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The getHeaders functions on these two methods just return the internal store of headers. Unfortunately, they store the data differently.</p>

<p>Zend_Controller_Response_Abstract:  Array of headers. Each header is an array with keys 'name' and 'value'
Zend_Http_Response: Headers are stored in an array in the form 'name' =&gt; 'value' (  line 170:  $this-&gt;headers[ucwords(strtolower($name))] = $value; )</p>

<p>It would seem to make sense for them to be harmonised.</p>

